title: Qualifying results for Folds of Honor QuikTrip 500 at Atlanta
text:
Mar 3, 2017 at 6:55p ET 0Shares 
Kevin Harvick will start from the pole in Sunday's Folds of Honor QuikTrip 500 at Atlanta Motor Speedway after he was fastest in Friday qualifying in his No. 4 Stewart-Haas Racing Ford. 
Check out the complete qualifying results and who will start where on Sunday: , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty 1 Kevin Harvick 
Harvick's fast lap of 190.398 miles per hour in Round 3 of qualifying is what won him the pole for Sunday's race.Kevin , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Barry Cantrell 2 Ryan Newman 
Newman narrowly missed out on winning the pole, but was pleased to find speed in his No. 31 Richard Childress Racing Chevrolet. His top lap in Round 3 was 189.870 mph. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Barry Cantrell 3 
Kyle Busch will start third on Sunday after a strong qualifying effort. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 4 Ricky Stenhouse Jr. 
Stenhouse has been suprisingly fast all weekend thus far in his No. 17 Roush Fenway Racing Ford and will roll off fourth Sunday. 5 
Team Penske's Keselowski will start fifth. 6 
Sticking close to his Team Penske teammate, Logano will start sixth. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 7 
Chip Ganassi Racing's Jamie McMurray was quick in qualifying and will start seventh. 8 
Larson also stuck close to his Ganassi teammate, McMurray, and will start eighth. 9 
Truex will start ninth in his No. 78 Furniture Row Racing Toyota. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Barry Cantrell 10 
Hamlin will start 10th in his No. 11 Joe Gibbs Racing Toyota. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Nigel Kinrade 11 Chase Elliott 
Elliott, who won the pole for the season-opening Daytona 500 last Sunday, at least advanced to the final round Friday. He'll start 11th. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 12 Dale Earnhardt Jr. 
Earnhardt made it to Round 3 of qualifying, but recorded the slowest lap of the 12 drivers to make the final round. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Nigel Kinrade 13 Kurt Busch 
The winner of last Sunday's Daytona 500 battled a loose car in the second round of qualifying, and was the last car eliminated from moving onto the final round. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 14 
Blaney narrowly missed making the final round of qualifying and will start 14th. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 15 
Bayne will roll off 15th in his No. 6 Roush Fenway Racing Ford on Sunday. 16 
Kenseth will start 16th in his No. 20 Joe Gibbs Racing Toyota. 17 
Menard will start 17th on Sunday in his No. 27 Richard Childress Racing Chevy. 18 Jimmie Johnson 
Johnson has won five times at Atlanta, including the last two. But he couldn't make it out of the second round of qualifying -- although he was quick to remind FOX Sports that he didn't qualify all that well the last two times he's won at AMS, either. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 19 Austin Dillon 
Dillon, the older of the two racing Dillon brothers, will start 19th. At least he made it past the first round of qualifying. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Barry Cantrell 20 
Allmendinger will roll off 20th in his No. 47 JTG Daugherty Racing Chevy. 21 Daniel Suarez 
The Cup rookie driver for Joe Gibbs Racing got some pre-qualifying advice from Carl Edwards, the former driver of the No. 19 Suarez now pilots. It may have helped some, but not enough. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Nigel Kinrade 22 Matt DiBenedetto 
For DiBenedetto, it was a minor triumph just to make it past the first round of qualfying -- but he could not make it out of the second. 23 Erik Jones 
The Cup rookie driver for Furniture Row Racing will start 23rd in his No. 77 Toyota. 24 Danica Patrick 
Patrick said her car was too loose and she had trouble seeing going into Turn 1 because the setting sun was in her eyes. She will start 24th. 25 Clint Bowyer 
Bowyer was disappointed to be the last driver knocked out in the first round of qualifying, as a late fast lap by Austin Dillon eliminated him. He will start 25th Sunday. 26 Ty Dillon 
Ty Dillon (right) tried to soak up some pre-qualifying advice from Hall of Famer Richard Petty (left). It must not have sunk in. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 27 
Cassill will start 27th in his No 34 Ford. 28 
Buescher, AJ Allmendinger's new teammate at JTG Daugherty Racing, will roll off 28th Sunday. 29 Kasey Kahne 
Kahne, whose last Cup win came at Atlanta in 2013, usually is fast at the track. But not in Friday qualifying. 30 
Almirola will start 30th in Sunday's race in his No. 43 Ford. 31 Gray Gaulding 
The Monster Energy NASCAR Cup Series rookie will roll off in 31st in his No. 23 Toyota on Sunday. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 32
